Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision, consecutive to any sentence presently being served.
The court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) No contact with any known drug dealers or users;
2) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same
7) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process
8) Obtain high school diploma/GED.
Minutes.
